# NextJS + TailwindCSS + MongoDB Project

This project is a modern web application built with:
- [NextJS](mdc:https:/nextjs.org) for the frontend framework
- [TailwindCSS](mdc:https:/tailwindcss.com) for styling
- [MongoDB](mdc:https:/www.mongodb.com) for the database

## Key Project Structure

The project follows a standard NextJS App Router structure:

- `frontend/src/app` - Main application code using the App Router pattern
- `frontend/src/app/page.tsx` - The main entry page for the application
- `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx` - The root layout that wraps all pages
- `frontend/src/app/globals.css` - Global CSS styles (includes Tailwind)

## Architecture Overview

This NextJS application follows these architectural principles:
1. **App Router** - Uses the newer App Router pattern instead of Pages Router
2. **Server Components** - Leverages React Server Components by default
3. **API Routes** - Will use API routes for backend functionality
4. **MongoDB Integration** - Connects to MongoDB for data storage
